The paper deals with a graph-based metric on points in Euclidean space, which is a topic that falls under computational geometry (cs.CG) and graph theory (cs.DS). The paper also discusses the density-sensitive property of the metric, which is relevant to machine learning (cs.LG) and information theory (cs.IT). Finally, the paper presents algorithms for computing sparse spanners of the distance, which is a problem in graph theory and computational geometry.
